docs.snippet: WASHINGTON, Aug. 15. -- The official statistics of the wheat crop of the world for 1899-1900 have just been compiled by the Department of Agriculture. They show that in the countries of the southern hemisphere whose wheat crops are commonly included...
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Aug. 15. -- The official statistics of the wheat crop of the world for 1899-1900 have just been compiled by the Department of Agriculture. They show that in the countries of the southern hemisphere whose wheat crops are commonly included in statements of the world's wheat crops the production will hardly fall less than 160,543,000 bushels.
